FILES

main.tf: 
Configuration file where you will define your infrastructure resources such as virtual machines, storage and networking components. 

provider.tf: 
Contains the provider configuration, like specifying which cloud provider (AWS, Azure, GCP, etc.) you're using, or any other third-party services.

variables.tf: 
Used to define input variables for the configuration. It helps to make the configuration flexible by allowing external values to be passed in.

outputs.tf: 
Contains the output values that are derived from the configuration. It allows you to extract and return useful information about your resources.

terraform.tfvars or *.auto.tfvars: 
Used to set values for the variables defined in variables.tf. This file can be used to define environment-specific settings or defaults.
